image.altText: A boy wearing green pajamas poses for a photo in a hospital

props.synopsis: The family of a four-year-old Perth boy who received serious facial injuries and nerve damage after being attacked by a pet dog while playing at friends house is questioning why the dog will not be destroyed.

title.children: Boy left with 'horrific' facial injuries after being mauled by friend's pet dog in Perth

image.altText: Image of a photograph of Josh Warneke placed in front of a memorial in Broome, Western Australia.

props.synopsis: There was no evidence to suggest a 21-year-old man found dead by the side of a road in the WA town of Broome in 2010 had been hit by a vehicle, an inquest into his death hears.

title.children: Highly unlikely Josh Warneke hit by car, crash investigator tells coronial inquest

image.altText: Faded red gas well head behind barbed wire fence

image.altText: Portrait of woman sitting on a couch holding a white mug of tea

title.children: Forced to switch off gas, this small WA seaside town became a 'microcosm of what the world is trying to do'

image.altText: A farmer, wearing an orange shirt and a hat, looks at his phone while standing in front of a shed.

props.synopsis: Australia's national unemployment rate remained steady in August at 4.2 per cent. The data comes after the US Federal Reserve cut rates by 50bp, sending US stocks lower, but the ASX200 lifted higher when the market opened.

image.altText: An Australian senator in a red jacket.

image.altText: Isaac Heeney, Zak Butters, Jeremy Cameron, Joe Daniher

image.altText: A pregnant woman receives her COVID-19 shot in Pennsylvania, January 2021.

image.altText: A graphic of Betty Shanks photo with newspaper clippings following her death around it.
